  "body": "- [x] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle)\r\n\r\nIt would be nice to be able to get a list of plugins that are installed other than looking at the truffle configuration file. \r\n\r\nIs there a preferred way for a plugin to provide help for it? In the example of https://github.com/trufflesuite/trufflesuite.com/issues/1396 I used `console.log` after looking at `config.help`, but is that recommended? For the core commands, their help is formatted in a uniform way, right? ",
